		 Saturday, October 05, 2002 				 ICC emphasis on recognition 
																								London, Oct. 4 (AP): Player associations must be recognised by their own boards before an umbrella group can discuss issues directly with the ICC.																								ICC president Malcolm Gray today said that until this was done, they could not deal with the Federation of International Cricketers Association (Fica).																								Morgan ECB boss																								David Morgan was today unanimously elected chairman of the ECB.
